
[1]lyrical

   LYR'ICAL, a. [L. lyricus.] Pertaining to a lyre or harp. Lyric poetry
   is such as is sung to the harp or lyre. This was much cultivated by the
   ancients, among whom Anacreon, Alcoeus, Stesichorus, Sappho and Horace
   are distinguished as lyric poets.
